    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory corruption in NGAP NAS non-delivery indication handling\n\n### Summary\nThe NGAP gNB implementation contained a critical memory management issue in the `ngap_gNB_nas_non_delivery_ind` function that could lead to crashes or undefined behavior under certain network conditions.\n\nThe bug occurred because the function was directly referencing buffer pointers from input parameters instead of making copies of the data. When the NGAP encoder later attempted to free the PDU contents, it would try to free memory that it didn't own.\n\nThis issue was particularly likely to manifest when handling NAS non-delivery indications during RRC connection reconfiguration procedures.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_nas_procedures.c`: Fixed buffer handling in `ngap_gNB_nas_non_delivery_ind` function\n- `openair3/NGAP/ngap_gNB_nas_procedures.c`: Applied same fix to `ngap_gNB_nas_uplink` function for consistency\n\n"
}